1. WCSLIB — code adapted (not linked)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Component:   WCSLIB 8.2 (`prj.c` — celestial projection routines)
Copyright:   Copyright (C) 1995-2024 Mark Calabretta, CSIRO/ATNF
Project:     https://www.atnf.csiro.au/people/mcalabre/WCS/
License:     LGPL-3.0-or-later

The WCS pixel→sky projection formulas (TAN, SIN, ARC, STG, CAR, MER,
GLS/SFL, AIT) implemented in `src/core/FitsImage.cpp` were adapted from
WCSLIB 8.2 (`prj.c`), as documented in a source comment at the top of
that file ("Projection formulas adapted from WCSLIB 8.2 (prj.c,
Calabretta, CSIRO ATNF)."). WCSLIB itself is not linked or bundled;
only the projection formulas were reimplemented in-house in C++,
following the mathematical treatment of Calabretta & Greisen (2002),
A&A 395, 1077 ("WCS Paper II"), which is the same reference WCSLIB
itself implements.

Because the adaptation follows WCSLIB's own reference implementation
rather than only the published paper, this NOTICE records the
derivation and the LGPL-3.0-or-later attribution duty as a matter of
diligence (AUD-PROV-1). LGPL-3.0 is a library-linking license; it does
not require AstroFind (an application, not a redistributed copy of the
library) to be relicensed, but does require that Calabretta's copyright
and the license be acknowledged wherever the adapted code is
distributed — which this NOTICE does.

